If a user changes the name of a page, you get a new entry in the page history with nothing indicating that the page was renamed. Clicking on "view changes" provides no information as to what changed.

It would be good if page renames left a record in the history of the previous name so you could see what had happened.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-4197].
  {panel}

If a user changes the name of a page that is linked to by a second page, the second page will show up in the dashboard as recently edited and the user will be listed as the last editor in the page history, but there is no entry in the "recent changes" to indicate what was changed.

It would be better if the version history indicates that this change was an automatic change as the result of the page rename.
